The paper involves the application of machine learning techniques, specifically Graph Neural Networks (GNN), to solve symbolic reasoning problems. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with Quantified Boolean Formula (QBF) problems, which are a type of propositional logic problem, indicating that the paper may also belong to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the feasibility of learning GNN-based heuristics for QBF problems, which involves software engineering and system design aspects, suggesting that the paper may also belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category.
